This Privacy Policy explains how Silly Games ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, stores, and protects personal data when you play OG Fun Monke Horror on Meta Quest devices. This policy applies to all players worldwide. We are committed to handling your personal data responsibly and in accordance with applicable privacy and data protection laws in your region.


By downloading or playing OG Fun Monke Horror, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please do not install or play the game.


1. Definitions

The following terms are used throughout this Privacy Policy:

"Device ID / Hardware ID" – A unique numerical identifier assigned to your specific device or system, used for account authentication.

"IP Address" – A unique numerical address that identifies your internet connection.

"User ID" – A unique identifier tied to your account, assigned by PlayFab or Meta.

"User Profile" – Account-associated information such as your display name and avatar.

"In-App Purchases" – Records of purchases made through Meta's platform for in-game items, including cosmetics and other content.

"Meta Challenges / Oculus Challenges" – Authentication mechanisms provided by Meta used to verify player legitimacy and maintain fair play.

"User Data" or "Developer User Data" – Any personal data collected, processed, or stored by us in connection with your use of OG Fun Monke Horror, as defined in Meta's Developer Data Use Policy.


2. Data We Collect

We collect only the minimum data necessary to provide the game and its features, in accordance with Meta's Developer Data Use Policy and applicable law. We collect the following categories of data:

A. Device ID / Hardware ID

Collected to authenticate your device and log you into your PlayFab / OG Fun Monke Horror account. This data is processed by PlayFab (a Microsoft service).

B. IP Address

Your IP address is stored within your PlayFab account record. It is used exclusively for in-game moderation purposes, such as enforcing IP bans against players who violate our rules. We do not use your IP address for advertising or tracking.

C. User ID

A unique identifier linked to your account, collected from PlayFab or Meta. Used for login, account management, and authentication purposes.

D. User Profile

Includes your in-game display name. Tied to your User ID for identification and login. Your display name may be visible to other players within the game.

E. In-App Purchases

Purchase records are provided to us by Meta when you buy in-game items. This data is used solely to confirm your transaction and deliver purchased content to your account. We do not independently store payment card details — payment processing is handled entirely by Meta.

F. Meta Challenges / Oculus Challenges Data

We may request access to Oculus Challenges data solely for authentication, account integrity verification, and ensuring fair play. This data is not used for advertising, profiling, or any other purpose, and is not sold or shared with third parties beyond what is necessary to operate these features.


3. How We Use Your Data

We use your data only for the purposes described below. We will not process your data in ways that are inconsistent with those purposes or beyond what is described in this policy. We do not sell your personal data to any third party.

- To authenticate your identity and log you into your account.

- To deliver in-game content and items you have purchased.

- To operate in-game moderation systems, including banning players who violate our Terms of Service.

- To verify player legitimacy and maintain fair play standards.

- To comply with our legal obligations under applicable law.


Legal basis for processing (GDPR): Where applicable, we rely on contract performance (to deliver the game experience you signed up for), legitimate interests (moderation and security), and legal obligation as our legal bases for processing your data. We do not rely on consent as a basis for processing data that is necessary to provide the game.


