5. Data Sharing

We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data. We may share your data only in the following limited circumstances:

- With our third-party service providers (PlayFab, Photon, Meta) as described in Section 4, strictly to operate the game.

- Where required by applicable law, court order, or regulatory authority.

- To protect the rights, safety, or property of Silly Games, our players, or others.


We do not share your data with advertisers or use your data for targeted advertising.


6. Data Retention

We retain your personal data for as long as your account remains active, or as long as necessary to provide the game's services. Specifically:

- Account data (User ID, Hardware ID, User Profile) is retained for the lifetime of your active account.

- IP address and moderation logs may be retained for a reasonable period to support moderation actions and appeals.

- Purchase records may be retained for longer periods where required by financial or tax law.


If you request deletion of your account, we will act on your request without undue delay, and will direct PlayFab to delete associated data in accordance with Meta's Developer Data Use Policy and PlayFab's data deletion obligations. Certain data may be retained longer if required by law or to resolve outstanding disputes.


7. Your Rights and Data Deletion

Regardless of your location, you have the right to request deletion of your personal data that we have collected or stored. This is a core requirement of Meta's VRC Privacy Standards (VRC.Quest.Privacy.4) and we honor it globally. To request deletion of your data and the removal of your PlayFab account from our servers, contact us at:

Email: bloxianforever@gmail.com

We will not charge you a fee for submitting a deletion request. We will respond to your request within a reasonable timeframe. We will explain clearly if any portion of your data cannot be deleted (for example, transaction records we are legally required to retain).

Depending on your jurisdiction, you may also have the right to:

- Access the personal data we hold about you.

- Request correction of inaccurate data.

- Object to or restrict certain processing of your data.

- Lodge a complaint with a data protection authority (EU/UK users).

- Opt out of the sale of personal data (we do not sell data, so this right is always satisfied).


To exercise any of these rights, contact us using the details in Section 9.


8. Children's Privacy

OG Fun Monke Horror is intended for users who meet Meta's minimum age requirement, which is 10 years of age or older (age requirements may vary by region). We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 10. If you believe a child under 10 has provided us with personal data, please contact us immediately and we will take steps to delete that information. If you are between 10 and 12 years old, your account must be set up and managed by a parent or guardian through Meta's parent-managed account system. If you are between 13 and 17, parental consent may still be required in accordance with Meta's policies and the laws of your jurisdiction. Meta's platform includes Family Center controls for parental oversight of younger users' accounts.


9. Data Security

We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. Your data is stored and processed through PlayFab (Microsoft), which implements industry-standard security controls as described in their security documentation.

We cannot guarantee absolute security of data transmitted over the internet. If you become aware of any security issue, please contact us promptly.


